originalText.text: This is the 2nd time my car was hit in 2 weeks in this parking garage. Today was unreal.  The trunk was destroyed.  I was in a bind  and needed to put the car in a lot.  Well I was smart enough to take before photos.. After waiting an hour to get the car it was smashed in.  Seems someone drove it under something and pull it out.  Including the paint.  The attendant denied the damage. Then the attendant that parked called me and tried to scam me. Told me to bring the car in he would check the damage. he would check his video . Where did my car go?  I sure didn’t take it out from the time I left it and the time I picked it up ?? Did some elf’s do it?  He is not an insurance company. Slick, scamming snakes. Supervisor Michael only comes in a midnight.  The rest of the employees act like they don’t know anything. They play stupid. If I could rate them with a negative number I would.  Police came and the employee acted stupid!  Nothing accomplished.  I will have to call the better business bureau.  Small claims court.  Just go that route can’t speak to this breed ! They are trying to tell me nothing happened in there.

originalText.text:
Writing a new review because my last one was deleted when this company tried to get rid of all its past bad reviews.

Useless automated garage that rarely works. I’ve been a monthly parker here only because I’m a resident in the building next door. If I had any other option for parking I would go elsewhere. Constantly broken down, loses cars, no technicians or attendants on site so you wait forever for them to figure out what is wrong. No compensation for their constant failures. AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

originalText.text: The garage manager has been so accommodating, checking in on us when our schedule routine may have been impacted by the snow and double checked the night before if we needed our car to be pulled out. The attendants have been great and everyone wears their mask. This garage for the price has been outstanding and the people who work here have been amazing. We have never received the car late, in fact the car is always ready for us, pulled to the side when we call 10 minutes in advance.

originalText.text: Parked my car here and there is zero signage indicating the garage closes at 10pm.  Also, the attendant never informed me of such.  I was to be somewhere first thing in the morning 3 plus hours away and intended on leaving around 11pm to avoid traffic.  I went to get my car and discovered the garage was closed and the doorman of the building told me they closed up for the night at 10pm and will not open until 7am, essentially holding my car hostage, screwing up my plans and making me late.  I had to get a cab to my friends place and she now has to drive me to where I need to be.  This is utterly insane and unprofessional.  And, the website also says 24hrs
